Package ohos.data.resultset

Interface ResultSet

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    SharedResultSet
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbsResultSet, AbsSharedResultSet, CombinedResultSet, ResultSetWrapper, TableResultSet

    public interface ResultSet
    Provides methods for accessing a database result set generated by querying the database.

    The abstract class AbsResultSet implements some methods in the ResultSet interface.

    Since:
    1
    See Also:
    AbsResultSet
    SystemCapability
    SystemCapability.Data#DATA_APPDATAMGR

    • Method Detail

      • getAllColumnNames

        String[] getAllColumnNames​()
        Obtains the names of all columns in a result set.

        The column names are returned as a string array, in which the strings are in the same order as the columns in the result set.

        Returns:
        Returns a string array containing all the column names in the result set.
        Since:
        1

      • getColumnCount

        int getColumnCount​()
        Obtains the number of columns in the result set.

        The returned number is equal to the length of the string array returned by the getAllColumnNames method.

        Returns:
        Returns the number of columns in the result set.
        Since:
        1
        See Also:
        getAllColumnNames()

        ResultSet.ColumnType getColumnTypeForIndex​(int columnIndex)

      • goTo

        boolean goTo​(int offset)
        Go to the specified row of the result set forwards or backwards by an offset relative to its current position. A positive offset indicates moving backwards, and a negative offset indicates moving forwards.
        Parameters:
        offset - Indicates the offset relative to the current position.
        Returns:
        Returns true if the result set is moved successfully and does not go beyond the range; returns false otherwise.
        Since:
        1

      • setAffectedByUris

        void setAffectedByUris​(Object context,
                       List<Uri> uris)
        Sets the URIs of the data to be observed.

        After setting the URIs, call the ResultSet#registerObserver method to register an observer that listens for data changes.

        Parameters:
        context - Indicates the context.
        uris - Uri list to observe changes which affect this ResultSet.
        Since:
        2
        See Also:
        registerObserver(ohos.data.rdb.DataObserver)

      • getAffectedByUris

        List<Uri> getAffectedByUris​()
        Obtains the list of URIs registered to observe changes that affect the result set.

        The list of URIs is set using the ResultSet#setAffectedByUris method.

        Returns:
        Returns the list of URIs.
        Since:
        3

      • registerObserver

        void registerObserver​(DataObserver observer)
        Registers an observer that listens for data changes.

        When a notification of the change of data with a specified URI is received, this observer will be triggered.

        Parameters:
        observer - Indicates the observer to be registered.
        Since:
        2
        See Also:
        setAffectedByUris(java.lang.Object, java.util.List<ohos.utils.net.Uri>), unregisterObserver(ohos.data.rdb.DataObserver)

      • unregisterObserver

        void unregisterObserver​(DataObserver observer)
        Deregisters an observer that listens for data changes.

        This method is used to release the observer before the component to which the observer belongs is destroyed.

        Parameters:
        observer - Indicates the observer to be deregistered.
        Since:
        2
